## Steps

### step 1
id: navigate-to-encounters
instruction: Click "Encounters" in the main sidebar, or use Cmd+K (Mac) / Ctrl+K (Windows) and type "Encounters" to navigate there.
success_criteria: You are on the Encounters page with a search bar and a list of encounters.
anchor: "Encounters"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Use the command palette (Cmd+K / Ctrl+K) if you can't find Encounters in the sidebar directly.

### step 2
id: search-for-encounter
instruction: Type the patient name or encounter number in the search bar. Results filter as you type.
success_criteria: Matching encounters are displayed in the list below.
anchor: "search bar"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Click the search bar and start typing. Results update in real-time.

### step 3
id: filter-by-status
instruction: Optionally use the status filter tabs above the list (e.g., Open, Submitted, Paid, Denied) to narrow results further.
success_criteria: The encounter you're looking for is visible in the filtered list.
anchor: "status filter"
on_success: next
on_stuck: Status filter tabs are above the encounter list.

### step 4
id: click-encounter
instruction: Click on the encounter row to open its detail page.
success_criteria: You are on the encounter detail page showing date of service, patient, provider, payer, and tabs for Details, Activity, and Documents.
anchor: "encounter row"
on_success: completion
on_stuck: Click anywhere on the row.

## Completion Message
found it. the encounter detail page shows the full claim, payment history, any denials, and all attached documents.

